Converb markers
WP:Converb
NOTE:These makers form subordinating clauses with adverbial function.
NOTE:Most of the suffixes that form converbs can also form other forms
NOTE:of subordination (verbal nouns and participles).
NOTE:Normally, the converbial markers has a restricted context, i.e.,
NOTE:they serve as cv only if they are followed by certain morphemes
NOTE:or words (particles). Current version of TRmorph does not 
NOTE:fully restrict these.
EX:gör-<b>mek</b> için gittim `I went in order to see'.
G&K:-CV
Type:Verbal/sub
